The project you've built is a static HTML + JavaScript website. It does not require any backend or complex dependencies, but here's a concise list of requirements for development and deployment:


---

System Requirements

1. Development Requirements (Local)

Text Editor:

VS Code (recommended)

Sublime Text, Atom, or even Notepad++


Browser:

Any modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)


Optional Tools:

Git (for version control and GitHub deployment)

Node.js (only needed if you plan to scale or add bundlers like Webpack later)




---

2. Deployment Requirements

For GitHub Pages

GitHub account

Git installed locally

Public repository for pushing files


For Netlify (No setup needed)

Netlify account (free)

Just drag & drop the folder



---

Project File Structure

tourism-analytics-demo/
│
├── index.html        # Main web page
├── app.js            # JavaScript functionality
└── README.md         # Project description (optional for GitHub)


---

Browser Compatibility

Fully works on:

Google Chrome

Firefox

Safari

Microsoft Edge


No server, backend, or frameworks required



